         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (This conversation now following, however, [must be]) understood [as taking place] in the palace of king Mahendrasena. There, too, ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #a7 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6 #b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>7ff</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">a3 ... she held fast the father’s heart. 1. Thereupon she ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... were to/for her. Thereupon the neighbouring kings of Jampudvīpa her ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... letters they wrote. || In the Ś.-tune: || You, pearl of women ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... princes ... Certainly you may give us (by) [your] virtue ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... with [his] chin in the palm of his hand he [= Mahendrasena] thought: ... since: || In the W.-tune(?): ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">b2 ... she [= Bhadrā] began, with flowers and circumambulation, (to honour(?) the Pratyekabuddha) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... to feel (the wish), she began. || In the A.-tune: || ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (when I die), may I be [re-]born as king Mahendrasena’s daughter ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the loves I enjoyed. You shall remember me. The six tusks ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (Thereupon) Bhadrā, the she-elephant, threw herself (?) from the mountain ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... doing penance for the love for the woman ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment">The translation is largely based on <bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>7-8</citedRange></bibl>, and <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#a5" type="lingcomment"><hi>pärsant</hi> from <hi>*pärs</hi> 'letter', cf. TB <hi>parso, pärso</hi> 'id.' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:couvreur1954b"/><citedRange>260</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment">The tune has 4x12 syllables, rhythm = 5/7.</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">The tune has 4x25 syllables, rhythm = 5/5/8/7.</note></p>
         </div>
